# Default install uses the PUBLIC npm registry for everything, so `npm install`
# works with no Font Awesome account: @fortawesome/fontawesome-free (a normal
# dependency) installs from public npm, and @fortawesome/fontawesome-pro (an
# optionalDependency) is simply skipped when it can't be resolved.
#
# Have a Font Awesome Pro account and want the Pro icon set? Do NOT add the Pro
# registry here (this file is committed). Instead copy .npmrc.pro.example into
# your USER-level ~/.npmrc and set FONTAWESOME_PACKAGE_TOKEN — see that file.
